-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Canadian Pacific Railway, Canaccord Genuity
-- 
-- Wed Jun 04, 2014 02:58AM EDT
-- None



June 4 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Canaccord Genuity, Canadian Pacific Railway and SNC-Lavalin Group, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS  * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: BMO raises to outperform from market perform  * Brazil Resources Inc <BRI.V>: Salman Partners starts with speculative buy rating   * Canaccord Genuity <CF.TO>: RBC raises price target to C$13 from C$12  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Brazil Resources Inc <BRI.V>: Salman Partners starts with speculative buy;target price C$2 * Canaccord Genuity <CF.TO>: RBC raises price target to C$13 from C$12; rating outperform  * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: BMO raises to outperform from market perform * Canadian Pacific Railway <CP.TO>: BMO raises target price to C$205 from C$180 * Canexus <CUS.TO>: National Bank Financial resumes coverage with underperform;target C$4.50 * Lundin Mining <LUN.TO>: National Bank Financial raises target price to C$6.25 from C$5.75 * SNC-Lavalin Group <SNC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target price to C$60 from C$63; buy